{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, OGB provides a unified format and interface for all datasets, as well as standardized.",
    "In OGB, ogbg-molhiv (Hu et al. 2020) and ogbg-molpcba (Hu et al. 2020) are molecular graph datasets for molecular property prediction.",
    "It contains a rich variety of organic molecular graphs and their corresponding bioactivity or chemical property labels, which provide important benchmarks for researchers to evaluate the ability of GNNs in drug discovery and chemistry.",
    "The ogbg-ppa (Hu et al. 2020) dataset focuses on the associative relationships between proteins, aiming to reveal the complex interaction networks between proteins through graph neural networks, and thus provide powerful support for research in bioinformatics and medicine.",
    "The ogbg-code2 (Hu et al. 2020) dataset contains Abstract Syntax Trees (ASTs) extracted from Python source code, which are tree-structured graphs that can effectively represent the syntactic and logical structure of the code."
  ]
}